import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['cx'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of boroughs by longitude?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sorted_data = data.sort_values(by='cx', ascending=False)
    ax = sorted_data.plot.bar(x='name', y='cx', legend=False)
    ax.set_ylabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_xlabel('Borough')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.axhline(y=sorted_data['cx'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max Longitude: {sorted_data['cx'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("Which borough has the highest longitude value?")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
